[{"id":"hv0504","cat":"algebra","topic":"Differentiation","q":"Differentiate $y = 4x^5$.","o":["$20x^4$","$4x^4$","$5x^4$","$20x^5$"],"a":0,"e":"$\\frac{dy}{dx} = 4 \\times 5x^{5-1} = 20x^4$.","d":1,"s":"Y11.6","diag":"calc"},{"id":"hv0505","cat":"algebra","topic":"Differentiation","q":"Differentiate $y = 7x^2$.","o":["$7x$","$14x^2$","$14x$","$2x$"],"a":2,"e":"$\\frac{dy}{dx} = 7 \\times 2x^{2-1} = 14x$.","d":1,"s":"Y11.6","diag":"calc"},{"id":"hv0506","cat":"algebra","topic":"Differentiation","q":"Differentiate $y = 2x^6$.","o":["$6x^5$","$12x^6$","$12x^5$","$12x^7$"],"a":2,"e":"$\\frac{dy}{dx} = 2 \\times 6x^{6-1} = 12x^5$.","d":1,"s":"Y11.6","diag":"calc"},{"id":"hv0507","cat":"algebra","topic":"Differentiation","q":"If the gradient of a curve at a certain point is zero, what is the value of $\\frac{dy}{dx}$ at that point?","o":["$1$","$0$","undefined","infinite"],"a":1,"e":"The gradient of a curve is given by $\\frac{dy}{dx}$. If the gradient is zero, then $\\frac{dy}{dx} = 0$.","d":1,"s":"Y11.6","diag":"concept"},{"id":"hv0508","cat":"algebra","topic":"Differentiation","q":"Which of the following describes a point on a curve where $\\frac{dy}{dx} = 0$?","o":["An $x$-intercept","A $y$-intercept","A stationary point","A point of inflection only"],"a":2,"e":"$\\frac{dy}{dx} = 0$ identifies a stationary point (such as a maximum, minimum, or stationary point of inflection) where the gradient is zero.","d":1,"s":"Y11.6","diag":"concept"},{"id":"hv0509","cat":"algebra","topic":"Differentiation","q":"What is true about the tangent to a curve at a stationary point?","o":["It is horizontal (gradient = 0)","It is vertical","It passes through the origin","It is parallel to the $y$-axis"],"a":0,"e":"At a stationary point, $\\frac{dy}{dx} = 0$, which means the tangent line is horizontal.","d":1,"s":"Y11.6","diag":"concept"},{"id":"hv0510","cat":"algebra","topic":"Differentiation","q":"$y = x^3 - 3x^2 - 9x + 5$. Find the $x$-coordinates of the stationary points.","o":["$x = 3$ and $x = -1$","$x = -3$ and $x = 1$","$x = 0$ and $x = 3$","$x = 3$ and $x = 9$"],"a":0,"e":"$\\frac{dy}{dx} = 3x^2 - 6x - 9 = 3(x^2 - 2x - 3) = 3(x-3)(x+1) = 0$. So $x = 3$ or $x = -1$.","d":2,"s":"Y11.6","diag":"calc"},{"id":"hv0511","cat":"algebra","topic":"Differentiation","q":"$y = x^3 - 12x + 7$. Find the $x$-coordinates of the stationary points.","o":["$x = 2$ and $x = -2$","$x = 4$ and $x = -4$","$x = 0$ and $x = 12$","$x = 3$ and $x = -3$"],"a":0,"e":"$\\frac{dy}{dx} = 3x^2 - 12 = 3(x^2 - 4) = 3(x-2)(x+2) = 0$. So $x = 2$ or $x = -2$.","d":2,"s":"Y11.6","diag":"calc"},{"id":"hv0512","cat":"algebra","topic":"Differentiation","q":"$y = 2x^3 - 15x^2 + 24x - 1$. Find the $x$-coordinates of the stationary points.","o":["$x = 1$ and $x = 4$","$x = 2$ and $x = 4$","$x = -1$ and $x = -4$","$x = 1$ and $x = 5$"],"a":0,"e":"$\\frac{dy}{dx} = 6x^2 - 30x + 24 = 6(x^2 - 5x + 4) = 6(x-1)(x-4) = 0$. So $x = 1$ or $x = 4$.","d":2,"s":"Y11.6","diag":"calc"},{"id":"hv0513","cat":"algebra","topic":"Differentiation","q":"$y = x^2 + 4x - 5$. Find the equation of the tangent at $x = 1$.","o":["$y = 6x - 6$","$y = 6x + 6$","$y = 2x - 2$","$y = 6x - 5$"],"a":0,"e":"$\\frac{dy}{dx} = 2x + 4$. At $x=1$, gradient $m = 6$. At $x=1$, $y = 1 + 4 - 5 = 0$. Tangent: $y - 0 = 6(x - 1)$, so $y = 6x - 6$.","d":2,"s":"Y11.6","diag":"calc"},{"id":"hv0514","cat":"algebra","topic":"Differentiation","q":"$y = 3x^2 - 2x + 1$. Find the equation of the tangent at $x = 2$.","o":["$y = 10x - 11$","$y = 10x - 13$","$y = 10x + 9$","$y = 6x - 3$"],"a":0,"e":"$\\frac{dy}{dx} = 6x - 2$. At $x=2$, gradient $m = 10$. At $x=2$, $y = 3(4) - 2(2) + 1 = 9$. Tangent: $y - 9 = 10(x - 2)$, so $y = 10x - 20 + 9 = 10x - 11$.","d":2,"s":"Y11.6","diag":"calc"},{"id":"hv0515","cat":"algebra","topic":"Differentiation","q":"$y = 2x^2 - 5x + 2$. Find the equation of the tangent at $x = 2$.","o":["$y = 3x - 6$","$y = 3x + 6$","$y = 8x - 16$","$y = 3x - 2$"],"a":0,"e":"$\\frac{dy}{dx} = 4x - 5$. At $x=2$, gradient $m = 3$. At $x=2$, $y = 2(4) - 5(2) + 2 = 0$. Tangent: $y - 0 = 3(x - 2)$, so $y = 3x - 6$.","d":2,"s":"Y11.6","diag":"calc"}]
